images.description: This tall, narrow hanging scroll features dark ink on silvery gray paper. It depicts a path ascending up a tall, craggy mountain. The mountain is lined with evergreen trees and shrubbery. Small wooden house-like structures stand around the base of the mountain. Animals graze outside one building at foreground left. More structures appear to occupy some higher-elevation areas as well, but the large scale of the landscape makes it hard to see their detail. More tall, narrow peaks appear in the background in lighter pigment.
images.alttext: Gray-toned hanging scroll with painting of mountains, trees, and buildings

images.description: Crouched on a low bench, a woman leans over a wash basin filled with water, in which she scrubs a white garment. She wears a light blue dress,  a red and orange striped skirt, and an apron. She faces left, but looks toward us with a smile and a raised eyebrow. She has pale skin, blue eyes and rosy cheeks, and her blonde hair is tucked into her frilled white bonnet. Beside the basin is a pitcher on a stool, and cluttered around her are a basket, a sheet hung over a cabinet to dry, and other basins.
images.alttext: A woman smiles as she sits stooped in front of a basin washing articles of clothing

images.copyright: President and Fellows of Harvard College
images.description: The scene has an overall muted brown tone and depicts several individuals, visible from head to toe, examining artworks in an outdoor stall. The brush strokes are suggestive, with some definition. Below a narrow black canopy is a light skinned woman in a black and white bonnet, and to her left is a light skinned man wearing a black top hat and long coat. His face is visible in profile as he looks at a panel of several artworks. Standing in front of them are two children. Toward the back right, a figure is clad in muted red.
images.alttext: Loose brush oil painting of several individuals looking at artworks in an outdoor market stall.

images.copyright: President and Fellows of Harvard College
President and Fellows of Harvard College
images.description: A head and shoulders portrait of a fair skinned man, is rendered with blocky, individual brushstrokes. He is shown facing us and looking to the right, his face made up of small swatches of pinks and tans, with pale green, gray and brown shadows. His neatly trimmed beard and mustache are dark brown, and his eyes almost black. He wears a high collared white shirt and a gray overcoat, shaded with brown and green. The background is a mottled blue-gray with lavender touches.
images.alttext: Portrait of a man with a beard and mustache

images.copyright: President and Fellows of Harvard College
images.description: At center right, an elderly man in a black hat with the brim flipped up, faces toward us but turns his head to the right, looking upward. He has a prominent nose, light skin and gaunt features. Gray hair peeking out from his hat is tied in back with a black ribbon, and he wears a red jacket with gold epaulets. Just behind him at center left, another man is identically dressed. He has pale skin, a full round face and gray curls protruding from his hat, as he looks up and to the left. The background is quickly brushed red and brown tones. Details at the edges of the canvas are left blank or rendered only in outline.
images.alttext: Double portrait of two men in black hats and red coats

images.copyright: President and Fellows of Harvard College
images.description: The woman has a placid look on her bright face, wearing a corseted coat dress with a grey swirl patterned bodice, black trim, white lace collar and cuffs. Her auburn hair is tucked under a matching hat. She faces to the right, looking to the right beyond us. She holds a child’s hand at the bottom left; painted in less detail. A man dressed in black is on the right, leaning in, looking out from the skating rink railing, towards the lady. A loosely painted crowd far in the background surrounds the rink, one man skates in midground.
images.alttext: Three-quarter portrait of a well-dressed fair skinned lady in the center at an outdoor skating rink.

images.description: A light-skinned, gray haired man faces the viewer, visible from the chest up. He has long gray hair that is tied back with a black ribbon. His eyes are blue, and his complexion is pink, especially around his cheeks and long, straight nose. His chin is slightly lifted. The man wears a ruffled white cravat and a dark coat with the lapels turned up. He sits before red drapery that is pulled to the left, revealing a cloudy blue sky. The light in this painting is soft and directional, highlighting the man’s face and leaving his torso mostly in shadow.
images.alttext: Painting of the head and shoulders of an older man with powdered hair and a dark coat
images.publiccaption: Gilbert Stuart, American, George Washington, c. 1795. Oil on canvas. Harvard University Portrait Collection, Gift of  Sidney F. Tyler to the University, 1969, H631.
